                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bacon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-29T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 29, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 29—5:30 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2190. Although CCP and PLA as such allotted only 18 seats on 89–man Presidium of
                    PCC, careful study of same list reveals at least 35 Presidium members are known
                    members CCP.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Peiping 375.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
